comments:
Great stay at Mary's for two nights! 

Room; 
We had 17. Was very clean, had toiletries, towels, TV, hairdryer and AC. You could lock the door for privacy. We had the air-con on thru the night so we didn't hear the music from the clubs while in the room altho Mary did provide earplugs.

Bathrooms; 
One toilet and another  toilet with shower on the second floor. Two toilets with showers on the first. You can use any of them. All very clean with good water pressure for the showers. We loved the fact there was an iron and board in one of them. And there was straighteners in another. Lovely touch.

Kitchen;
We didn't cook but there was space to and space to sit and eat. We did use the water cooler and the disposable cups that were provided. 

Location;
Mary's place is ideally located just off of Hollywood Boulevard. Capital Records, Walk of Fame, Chinese Theatre all within walking distance, Universal was 10 mins in an Uber. There's also plenty of bars and restaurants around. Mary recommended Kitchen 24 which was great. Yes there are some interesting characters on the boulevard but don't let that stop you going out and exploring, no one approached us or made us feel uncomfortable at any point. If you're not confident get ubers.

From LAX we got the bus which took around an hour and was $8, Mary will send the details. 

In general, we had a great stay, it was ideal having our own room and the location was perfect. We met Mary when checking out and she was lovely giving us more tips for our next place. 

No hesitation to recommend her place to anyone else. Thanks Mary!
